From Kevin Stamber Subject Re Radio stations In article Randy Graca writes Steve Greanias writes I do not have cable and on the nights the Caps don't play I would like to tune in other Does anyone have a list of the radio stations which broadcast the games for the NHL teams Thanks in advance I can give you a In Detroit WJR will be broadcasting at least the first couple of games of the Wings Toronto series and since they broadcast at Watts you may be able to pick it up after dark where you are The Pittsburgh Penguins games used to be broadcast on KDKA but I don't know whether they will be pre empted by baseball and moved to another station or You can try those if the local baseball teams aren't playing at the same time Randy KDKA has first rights to Pirates games and will split probably in conflicts for Penguins games which are preempted check out WDVE FM that's right DVE It is also Kevin Stamber Purdue University no funny today